description: Starts a job to import a resource to Amazon Lex.

parameters.name: payload
parameters.description: A zip archive in binary format. The archive should contain one file, a JSON file containing the resource to import. The resource should match the type specified in the resourceType field.

parameters.name: resourceType
parameters.description: Specifies the type of resource to export. Each resource also exports any resources that it depends on. A bot exports dependent intents. An intent exports dependent slot types.

parameters.name: mergeStrategy
parameters.description: Specifies the action that the StartImport operation should take when there is an existing resource with the same name. FAIL_ON_CONFLICT - The import operation is stopped on the first conflict between a resource in the import file and an existing resource. The name of the resource causing the conflict is in the failureReason field of the response to the GetImport operation. OVERWRITE_LATEST - The import operation proceeds even if there is a conflict with an existing resource. The $LASTEST version of the existing resource is overwritten with the data from the import file.

parameters.name: tags
parameters.description: A list of tags to add to the imported bot. You can only add tags when you import a bot, you can't add tags to an intent or slot type. (dict) --- A list of key/value pairs that identify a bot, bot alias, or bot channel. Tag keys and values can consist of Unicode letters, digits, white space, and any of the following symbols: _ . : / = + - @. The key for the tag. Keys are not case-sensitive and must be unique. The value associated with a key. The value may be an empty string but it can't be null.

nested_params.name: key
nested_params.description: The key for the tag. Keys are not case-sensitive and must be unique.

nested_params.name: value
nested_params.description: The value associated with a key. The value may be an empty string but it can't be null.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name given to the import job.

nested_items.name: resourceType
nested_items.description: The type of resource to import.

nested_items.name: mergeStrategy
nested_items.description: The action to take when there is a merge conflict.

nested_items.name: importId
nested_items.description: The identifier for the specific import job.

nested_items.name: importStatus
nested_items.description: The status of the import job. If the status is FAILED, you can get the reason for the failure using the GetImport operation.

nested_items.name: tags
nested_items.description: A list of tags added to the imported bot.

nested_items.name: key
nested_items.description: The key for the tag. Keys are not case-sensitive and must be unique.

nested_items.name: value
nested_items.description: The value associated with a key. The value may be an empty string but it can't be null.

nested_items.name: createdDate
nested_items.description: A timestamp for the date and time that the import job was requested.
